The paper proposes two neural network architectures for nested named entity recognition (NER), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses various deep learning techniques such as LSTM-CRF, sequence-to-sequence models, and contextual embeddings such as ELMo, BERT, and Flair, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
